      "text": "The first plants were aquatic, as described in the page [[Evolutionary History of Plants]], and released sperm freely into the water to be carried with the currents. Primitive land plants like liverworts and mosses had motile sperm that swam in a thin film of water or were splashed in water droplets from the male reproduction organs onto the female organs. "
    },
